{The bidding has been as shown.  

Your partner has shown a minimum opening hand, but with 6 \Ss. You are happy with the 8-card trump fit but need to know about Key-Cards. So you bid 4NT. Partner answers 5\S and it is your bid again. 

Partner has two Aces and the \SQ. That should be all he needs to make slam so you bid 6\S.}

